-- Ghana 91-day bill yield rises to 25.0174 percent
-- By Kwasi Kpodo
-- Fri Aug 08, 2014 01:46PM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, Aug 8 (Reuters) - The Bank of Ghana said the yield on its 91-day bill rose to a fresh three-year high of 25.0174 percent at Friday's auction, from 25.0104 percent at the last sale.

The Bank said it accepted all 1.51 billion cedis ($414 million) worth of bids tendered for the 91-day paper. For full details please click here:   http://www.bog.gov.gh/privatecontent/Treasury/Auctresults%201393.pdf ($1= 3.6200 cedis)   (Reporting by Kwasi Kpodo; editing by Daniel Flynn)  Keywords: GHANA BONDS/